entry.def: A three-dimensional object is solid rather than flat, because it can be measured in three different directions, usually the height, length, and width. The abbreviation 3-D can also be used.

entry.tran: (照片、图像、电影)三维的，有立体感的(缩略形式为 3-D)
entry.def: A three-dimensional picture, image, or film looks as though it is deep or solid rather than flat. The abbreviation 3-D can also be used.
